name: "C.H.U.D" Limited Edition T-shirt (SHIRT ONLY)
description: OUT OF THE SEWERS and INTO YOUR HOMES! Cannibalistic Humanoid Underground Dweller or as I call it; "Cannibalistic Humanoid Underground Dripper" C.H.U.D (1984) "There are monsters lurking beneath the streets; beings that were once human, but have been mutated by radioactive, chemical toxic waste into hideous, flesh-eatingcreatures that prey on the homeless who live in the underground. Given the recent drop in the underground transient population, the creatures have resorted to coming to the surface of the city, through sewer manholes in order to feed on the living" I've always wanted to do a proper tribute for this movie, and also giving the monster the respect it deserves by capturing the viciousness of what is known to lurk in the sewers! I watched this movie as a kid, and it never scared me, but I have always been fascinated by the idea of half human / half mutant monsters living under the streets, peaking through sewer drains, and snatching people down into their toxic world. THAT idea is terrifying. Who really know's what is living down there?! - Aaron C.H.U.D LIMITED EDITION T-shirt ONLY 100 AVAILABLE in this style. *THIS IS THE SHIRT by itself. You can also purchase the SHIRT / PRINT combo as well for only $20 more* a savings of $10. Item fits MEN & WOMEN check size chart for measurements. click here for size chart! name: "ECTOPLASM DESSERT" T-shirt (Limited Edition)
description: Other than being used by ghosts and demonic forces in the Ghostbusters to cover themselves with to be able to interact with us human's in this dimension, the term "ectoplasm" goes back far in time, and has been a sort of non proven substance which has appeared in many paranormal cases dating back to the 1800's. Some researchers even claim that the fluid exists in every living human being, and it could be released in the case that you are experiencing a paranormal interaction. Let's just say ghosts cover themselves in this substance sort of how you would wear a sheet over your body to look like a ghost. It gives them a physical presence in our world, and allows them to be seen. But instead of being seen as their actual human form, they're seen as a blob of gross, green, sloppy slime that wants to eat and eat and scream! Whether it's real or not, I made it real with this brand new T-shirt that is sure to scare kids into eating it year around! *note* After wearing this shirt, you may experience a bright green discharge from every hole in your body. Sorry! THIS ITEM IS STRICTLY LIMITED EDITION TO 100 SHIRTS only. Once they sell out, they are gone forever. Item fits MEN & WOMEN check size chart for measurements. click here for size chart! Soft 3 color screenprint on White 100% cotton American Apparel shirts. Tag us on your social network! #ectoplasm #cavitycolors #aaroncrawford

name: "CRITE BITE SUNDAE" T-shirt
description: The 80's was full of some of the absolute BEST horror / monsters movies of all time. Some say it was even the golden age of special effects, and I agree. Most of my favorite movies came out in that era for sure. It was the start of many popular franchise films, and slasher flicks became as common as butter and popcorn. With so many amazing and monstrous movies hitting our screens, one of them stood out as a gem in sci-fi / horror / creature movies, and that movie is CRITTERS! I first saw the original film as a child, and absolutely loved it. What's better then furry balls of hungry soccerball looking creatures from space eating their way through a tiny country town and terrorizing everyone with their sharp teeth and porcupine hair bodies, while also being hunted by 2 intergalactic police officers who look like hair band members. It was amazing, and still stands to be one of my favorite sci - fi horror movies of the era. In honor of the CRITES! We are unleashing the CRITE BITE SUNDAE! This is a Limited Edition item, so there's only a set amount available. It may never be reprinted in this style again! Item fits MEN & WOMEN Ultra soft screenprint on Black 100% cotton american apparel shirts. This item is Unisex. click here for size chart! Tag us on your social network! #cavitycolors #critebite#critters #aaroncrawford

name: "MONSTERHOUSE" T-shirt
description: "THE HOUSE IS ALIVE, and THE HOUSE IS HUNGRY" -the paper chase One of my favorite ideas of a monster has to be the thought of a house which is possessed by it's owners soul, or by something more sinister with worse intentions, transforming it into a towering beast for no reason at all. Maybe the person who died there is trapped forever and controls the walls and basement, who knows! But haunted houses are already really cool, so imagine a house with a stomach, teeth, a beating heart, a brain. I've always been obsessed with the idea of that, so I wanted to pay homage to all the possessed homes that are surrounding us on a daily basis! name: "Toxic Cavitycone" Ultra Limited Print
description:
Part of the "SUGAR SERIES" of paintings / prints - What would normally be delicious, mouth watering desserts, gone terribly wrong. Some of them are filled with acid and will melt your lips off, and some of them look normal until you bite in, and they bite back.
Destroying desserts, one painting at a time.

This is the TOXIC CAVITYCONE. 
If you can't tell if it's icecream or melted flesh? That's because it's BOTH!

<b>
"TOXIC CAVITYCONE"
Limited Edition of just 20 prints
Signed / Numbered by Aaron
Size: 13 x 16
Printed with Archival Inks on Velvet Cotton Rag

name: "COTTON CANDY COCOON OF SOULS" Limited Edition Poster
description:
The last print release of 2012!
A deliciously, horrific poster Inspired by Killer Klowns From Outer Space!
The COTTON CANDY COCOON OF SOULS Inspired by Killer Klowns From Outerspace, contains the poor souls of 3 victims who were viciously snatched up by the Killer Klowns, and forced into a Cocoon of acidic candy.
deep in the bowels of the gigantic Big Top Spaceship. And that's not even the worst part.....
Once inside the cocoon, each Klown uses a crazy straw to suck out all of your guts, turning you into a pile of empty flesh and candy string! What a horrible, but tasty way to be slaughtered
<b>
"COTTON CANDY COCOON OF SOULS" 
Limited edition of 50 prints 
Size: 13 x 16 inches 
Signed / Numbered by Aaron

name: "NEVADA MELTDOWN" Limited Edition poster
description:
<b>THE NEVADA MELTDOWN - By Aaron Crawford

This poster is inspired by the scene in the film where he takes acid right before they check into the Vegas hotel, and he’s sweating profusely and can barely speak at check in, and everyone in the lounge turns into giant bloody lizards and monsters. ‘IT WAS A GODDAMN REPTILE ZOO” was the quote, I think. Either way, this was always one of my favorite scenes in the movie. Hell, the entire movie is one of my favorites of all time. So, I wanted to honor that, and share this art with you all, cause I know a lot of you really appreciate the life and creativity Hunter Thompson brought to the world of Journalism and pop culture in general, plus the film that really captured his experiences in Nevada.

<b>
“THE NEVADA MELTDOWN”
Limited Giclee Print release

An Edition of Only 50 
Size: 13 x 16
Signed / Numbered by Aaron Crawford

name: "PIZZA THE SLUT" Limited Edition Print
description:
Ever since I saw Spaceballs, and the amazingly cheesy character PIZZA THE HUT, I've always thought about how amazing it would be if your skin was made of pizza toppings that you could just eat from whenever you were hungry. Well, I finally got around to drawing it and bringing the ridiculous idea to life.

That makes me a total slut for pizza, and ff you're a Pizzaslut too, then why not enjoy some on a print!
<b>
Size: 13 x 16

Limited to only 20 prints

Printed with archival inks on soft Velvet Cotton Rag

Signed & Numbered by Aaron
